comments: Washington (CHA) brings his right forearm toward Embiid's (PHI) side and marginal contact occurs after Embiid's gather.
Hayward (CHA) establishes himself in bounds before making contact with the ball.
Green (PHI) and Hayward (CHA) each make clean contact with the ball before any incidental arm contact occurs as they attempt to secure the ball.
Maxey (PHI) moves laterally into Hayward's (CHA) path and initiates body contact that affects Hayward's driving shot attempt.
Green (PHI) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Washington (CHA) is already in Curry's (PHI) path and he slightly re-establishes himself in Curry's path as Curry commits to going under the screen.
Embiid (PHI) briefly grasps Washington's (CHA) left arm and he immediately releases Washington's arm as he moves to set the pick.
Washington (CHA) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Martin (CHA) brushes Curry's (PHI) left arm as Curry gathers and marginal contact occurs before Martin cleanly deflects the ball.
Washington (CHA) initiates contact across Embiid's (PHI) left arm and causes him to lose control of the ball after his gather.

A jump ball is called to determine possession. Embiid (PHI) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds, and possession should be awarded to Charlotte.  Since a jump ball was assessed, the shot clock resets to :24.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) brushes Harris' (PHI) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Harris passes the ball.
Hayward (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball prior to any incidental arm contact occurring with Curry (PHI) as Curry makes the pass.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Harris (PHI) before any incidental contact occurs.
Bridges (CHA) extends his arm into Maxey's (PHI) path and initiates contact with Maxey's front before making contact with the ball.
Bridges (CHA) swipes his arm down and initiates contact across Curry's (PHI) left arm during the drive.
Green (PHI) legally contests Washington's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) releases away from Martin (CHA) and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Martin (CHA) brings his arm toward Maxey's (PHI) path and marginal contact occurs with Maxey's right arm as he starts his dribble.
Martin (CHA) swipes forward and cleanly deflects the ball away from Maxey (PHI). After the deflection, Martin and Maxey make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another.
Bridges (CHA) swipes down and initiates contact across Harris' (PHI) left leg after he receives the pass.
Washington (CHA) sets the pick on Maxey (PHI) and gives Maxey a step of distance to avoid the contact, which Washington absorbs.
Green (PHI) retreats alongside Hayward's (CHA) path and is bringing his arm into a vertical position as he absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) and Hayward (CHA) each make clean contact with the ball before any incidental arm contact occurs during rebounding.
Martin (CHA) commits a take foul on Embiid (PHI).
Philadelphia is assessed their second Delay of Game violation, which results in a technical foul free throw.
Correctly called Delay of Game violation on Philadelphia.
Embiid (PHI) and Washington (CHA) briefly engage and disengage with one another as Washington moves to set the screen.
Curry (PHI) and Oubre Jr. (CHA) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Washington (CHA) continues to re-establish himself towards Curry (PHI) and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Embiid (PHI) turns and initiates body contact with Oubre Jr. (CHA) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) and Maxey (PHI) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
